There's no way that pitiful explosion
could destroy this ship!

47
00:02:16.910 --> 00:02:19.330
You mean it didn't work?!

48
00:02:19.330 --> 00:02:22.660
Of course not! It didn't even leave a scratch!

49
00:02:23.290 --> 00:02:26.460
The sails got burned, though...

50
00:02:30.760 --> 00:02:32.760
Sorry, Kin'emon!

51
00:02:32.760 --> 00:02:35.550
It took us a while to patch them up!

52
00:02:35.550 --> 00:02:36.930
I see!

53
00:02:36.930 --> 00:02:38.850
So that is what happened!

54
00:02:38.850 --> 00:02:40.640
Hey, Kin!

55
00:02:41.470 --> 00:02:44.480
Weren't there supposed
to be way more of you?!

56
00:02:45.190 --> 00:02:47.690
That's a little different than what I heard.

57
00:02:47.690 --> 00:02:50.610
Anyway, I'm gonna wreck those ships, okay?!

58
00:02:51.070 --> 00:02:52.190
Indeed...

59
00:02:52.190 --> 00:02:55.700
We were expecting a lot more allies.

60
00:02:56.950 --> 00:03:00.330
What happened to the 3,500 prisoners
from the mining camp?!

61
00:03:00.330 --> 00:03:02.160
Yeah, I don't see them.

62
00:03:02.620 --> 00:03:06.120
The bosses traveled to different
regions to gather the yakuza...

63
00:03:06.120 --> 00:03:09.290
There must've been over 200 of them.

64
00:03:09.290 --> 00:03:13.840
At Itachi Port, there were
200 of Inuarashi's Musketeers,

65
00:03:13.840 --> 00:03:17.840
and 280 of the Mount Atama Thieves!

66
00:03:17.840 --> 00:03:22.430
Everyone was supposed to meet us here
on the ships we repaired together!

67
00:03:22.430 --> 00:03:26.640
Plus a cache of weapons large enough
to arm every last one of them…

68
00:03:26.640 --> 00:03:29.270
should've been delivered from Ringo!

69
00:03:29.690 --> 00:03:31.730
Hey, Kin'emon!

70
00:03:31.730 --> 00:03:33.150
Did you run into trouble?!

71
00:03:44.330 --> 00:03:48.000
I... made a grave error...

72
00:03:50.380 --> 00:03:52.420
Sir Luffy, I am sorry!

73
00:03:53.090 --> 00:03:56.590
Our entire plan was leaked...

74
00:03:58.130 --> 00:04:01.720
I have no idea what's befallen the others!

75
00:04:02.140 --> 00:04:04.220
So that's why nobody came!

76
00:04:04.220 --> 00:04:06.390
Does that mean we're alone in the fight?!

77
00:04:06.390 --> 00:04:08.980
What?! No way!

78
00:04:08.980 --> 00:04:11.520
We don't really know what's going on, either!

79
00:04:11.520 --> 00:04:14.900
We might've failed to destroy the lion ship...

80
00:04:14.900 --> 00:04:19.700
...but we sank all the ships
docked at the port last night!

81
00:04:19.700 --> 00:04:22.410
Lord Orochi is a meticulous man.

82
00:04:22.740 --> 00:04:26.370
He ordered us to destroy
every major bridge connecting the regions!

83
00:04:27.750 --> 00:04:29.580
Do you get it now?

84
00:04:29.580 --> 00:04:33.000
Nobody's coming to save you!

85
00:04:33.000 --> 00:04:38.420
Even if they could get here, they won't
be able to reach Onigashima without ships!

86
00:04:38.420 --> 00:04:42.470
And if you miss this opportunity,
you'll never get another chance!

87
00:04:42.470 --> 00:04:47.430
Tomorrow, we'll start killing all the rebels
that we lured out, one by one!

88
00:04:48.940 --> 00:04:52.440
There's one more thing
we haven't mentioned yet!

89
00:04:52.440 --> 00:04:53.940
I'm sorry.

90
00:04:53.940 --> 00:04:56.980
We didn't want to plunge
you further into despair...

91
00:04:57.530 --> 00:04:58.740
What?!

92
00:04:59.070 --> 00:05:03.490
Today's banquet isn't an
ordinary Fire Festival feast...

93
00:05:03.870 --> 00:05:06.240
It's also a celebration...

94
00:05:06.240 --> 00:05:11.210
of the alliance between us, the Beast Pirates,
and the infamous Big Mom Pirates!

95
00:05:13.130 --> 00:05:15.170
Kaido and Big Mom?!

96
00:05:15.170 --> 00:05:17.210
An alliance of two Emperors?!

97
00:05:17.210 --> 00:05:21.220
We have both Captain Kaido
and Big Mom on our side!

98
00:05:21.220 --> 00:05:23.970
How can they hope to match
that kind of might?!

99
00:05:23.970 --> 00:05:26.760
The Worst Generation?! They're nothing!

100
00:05:26.760 --> 00:05:30.480
Let's sink them all and finish this!

101
00:05:30.480 --> 00:05:31.850
Get ready to fire!

102
00:05:39.400 --> 00:05:41.950
Why are you acting all high and mighty?!

103
00:05:43.030 --> 00:05:44.530
I've heard enough!

104
00:05:44.530 --> 00:05:45.910
Everyone, stand back!

105
00:05:46.240 --> 00:05:47.490
Imbecile...

106
00:05:47.490 --> 00:05:48.870
You stand back!

107
00:05:49.120 --> 00:05:49.200
What are you doing, Traffy?!

108
00:05:49.200 --> 00:05:49.290
What are you doing, Traffy?!

109
00:05:49.290 --> 00:05:50.790
What are you doing, Traffy?!

110
00:05:50.790 --> 00:05:53.170
I said I'll do it!

111
00:05:53.170 --> 00:05:54.380
As if you even could!

112
00:05:54.380 --> 00:05:57.040
No, both of you stand back!

113
00:05:57.040 --> 00:05:58.420
I'll do it!

114
00:05:58.750 --> 00:06:00.880
Screw you, Jaggy!

115
00:06:00.880 --> 00:06:02.720
Shut your mouth!

116
00:06:02.720 --> 00:06:02.800
Quit interrupting, you morons!

117
00:06:02.800 --> 00:06:02.880
Quit interrupting, you morons!

118
00:06:02.880 --> 00:06:04.840
Quit interrupting, you morons!

119
00:06:04.840 --> 00:06:05.890
Sheesh!

120
00:06:05.890 --> 00:06:07.390
First one there wins!

121
00:06:07.390 --> 00:06:08.970
You bastard!

122
00:06:08.970 --> 00:06:10.980
I'll be the first!

123
00:06:10.980 --> 00:06:12.100
Like hell you will!

124
00:06:18.270 --> 00:06:19.320
Traffy!

125
00:06:19.320 --> 00:06:20.530
Why you...!

126
00:06:20.530 --> 00:06:22.990
You can't outpace my
Room ability in rain!

127
00:06:22.990 --> 00:06:26.870
That's cheating! Your ability isn't fair!

128
00:06:26.870 --> 00:06:27.870
Who cares?

129
00:06:27.870 --> 00:06:30.160
You're just showing off!

130
00:06:30.160 --> 00:06:31.750
Look who's talking.

131
00:06:31.750 --> 00:06:33.290
Go away!

132
00:06:33.290 --> 00:06:35.330
I can take them out with a single blow!

133
00:06:35.330 --> 00:06:39.960
Are you trying to say
I can't do it in one shot?!

134
00:06:40.380 --> 00:06:41.510
I'll do it.

135
00:06:41.510 --> 00:06:43.550
You two are losers.

136
00:06:43.550 --> 00:06:44.970
Any complaints?

137
00:06:44.970 --> 00:06:46.640
– Losers?!
– Losers?!

138
00:06:46.640 --> 00:06:48.260
Who are you calling loser?!

139
00:06:48.260 --> 00:06:50.310
I won't lose to anyone!

140
00:06:50.310 --> 00:06:51.770
Stay out of my way!

141
00:06:51.770 --> 00:06:55.230
Y-You better not expect to
make it out of here alive!

142
00:06:55.230 --> 00:06:57.400
Stop barking, flunkies!

143
00:06:57.400 --> 00:06:59.070
I'll take care of them.

144
00:06:59.570 --> 00:07:00.650
Shut up!

145
00:07:00.650 --> 00:07:01.980
We'll see who's a loser!

146
00:07:06.820 --> 00:07:07.660
Room!

147
00:07:39.610 --> 00:07:41.690
Boundman!

148
00:07:48.320 --> 00:07:50.280
Punk Vise!

149
00:08:01.090 --> 00:08:02.840
Injection Shot!

150
00:08:35.750 --> 00:08:37.120
Hey, did you see that?

151
00:08:37.120 --> 00:08:39.210
Who's a loser now?!

152
00:08:39.540 --> 00:08:41.500
Let me make one thing clear.

153
00:08:42.210 --> 00:08:44.920
I'm the one who sank that ship.

154
00:08:44.920 --> 00:08:46.920
Are you blind?!

155
00:08:47.340 --> 00:08:48.550
Don't be stupid!

156
00:08:48.550 --> 00:08:50.470
I sank it!

157
00:08:50.470 --> 00:08:53.640
I thought they were allies...

158
00:08:57.890 --> 00:08:58.600
What's that...?!

159
00:09:00.730 --> 00:09:02.810
The Kyoshiro Family's ship!

160
00:09:02.810 --> 00:09:05.070
Kyoshiro's here!

161
00:09:05.070 --> 00:09:07.530
Now the show can go on!

162
00:09:07.530 --> 00:09:09.860
Seems like you're in trouble.

163
00:09:09.860 --> 00:09:15.200
All we have to do is sink the Red Scabbards,
as Lord Orochi ordered us to!

164
00:09:15.580 --> 00:09:16.620
Alright.

165
00:09:16.620 --> 00:09:18.910
Sink the enemy, you say?

166
00:09:18.910 --> 00:09:20.000
Allow me!

167
00:09:24.880 --> 00:09:27.510
What are you doing, Boss?!

168
00:09:34.220 --> 00:09:36.220
There was no need to sink the ship.

169
00:09:36.220 --> 00:09:40.310
Though I did take the liberty of
disabling the cannons pointed at us.

170
00:09:40.310 --> 00:09:42.810
That guy... I remember him!

171
00:09:42.810 --> 00:09:45.820
Be careful! He's a master of the blade!

172
00:09:45.820 --> 00:09:48.070
He's the shogun's dog!

173
00:09:48.070 --> 00:09:51.780
A man of chivalry who took
the place of Boss Hyogoro!

174
00:09:54.740 --> 00:09:56.990
Red Scabbards samurai!

175
00:09:57.450 --> 00:10:00.700
I am a yakuza from the Flower Capital!

176
00:10:00.700 --> 00:10:03.420
People call me Napping Kyoshiro!

177
00:10:03.870 --> 00:10:09.590
The Kyoshiro Family is 200 strong!
Please allow us to join your raid!

178
00:10:10.380 --> 00:10:11.550
– What?!
– What?!

179
00:10:11.550 --> 00:10:13.090
You've gotta be kidding, Boss!

180
00:10:13.090 --> 00:10:14.510
What do you mean?!

181
00:10:14.510 --> 00:10:16.140
You're Orochi's subordinate!

182
00:10:16.140 --> 00:10:18.100
What obligation do you have to help us?

183
00:10:21.270 --> 00:10:26.020
The duty and gratitude I hold toward
the Kozuki Clan are immeasurable…

184
00:10:29.230 --> 00:10:31.940
I remember you especially, Kin!

185
00:10:32.860 --> 00:10:34.110
Kin?!

186
00:10:34.110 --> 00:10:38.490
Forty years ago, the Mountain God
Incident shook the capital!

187
00:10:41.910 --> 00:10:45.290
People blamed it on Lord Oden running wild...

188
00:10:46.170 --> 00:10:47.920
But they were wrong.

189
00:10:47.920 --> 00:10:54.800
You were the cause: a greedy young man
trying to sell a little boar!

190
00:10:59.220 --> 00:11:00.390
What?

191
00:11:00.390 --> 00:11:03.430
Only one man could possibly know that!

192
00:11:05.440 --> 00:11:08.270
That's why they call it the Mountain God!

193
00:11:08.270 --> 00:11:09.480
What?!

194
00:11:09.480 --> 00:11:11.400
Oh no!

195
00:11:11.400 --> 00:11:13.900
I've brought this upon the capital!

196
00:11:15.820 --> 00:11:16.950
Could it be...?

197
00:11:17.450 --> 00:11:18.950
Is that you, Denjiro?!

198
00:11:18.950 --> 00:11:19.580
What?!

199
00:11:19.580 --> 00:11:20.580
Denjiro?!

200
00:11:26.290 --> 00:11:28.080
Exactly right!

201
00:11:28.080 --> 00:11:29.920
I suppose you may not recognize me...

202
00:11:30.960 --> 00:11:33.510
I wanted to reveal myself to you right away,

203
00:11:33.510 --> 00:11:36.880
but I remained an enemy, just in case.

204
00:11:36.880 --> 00:11:39.760
Sure enough, if I had revealed my identity,

205
00:11:39.760 --> 00:11:44.640
I would've been exposed by
Orochi's spy and snuffed out!

206
00:11:46.350 --> 00:11:47.600
Denjiro!

207
00:11:47.600 --> 00:11:49.400
Silence!

208
00:11:49.400 --> 00:11:53.190
However, since I kept
Orochi's trust until the end,

209
00:11:53.190 --> 00:11:58.070
I was able to free the 1,000 samurai
from Rasetsu Prison!

210
00:11:58.070 --> 00:11:59.240
Look over there!

211
00:11:59.240 --> 00:12:00.410
Enemy reinforcements?!

212
00:12:02.030 --> 00:12:04.160
We now have 1,200 soldiers!

213
00:12:04.160 --> 00:12:06.410
Let us bolster your ranks!

214
00:12:12.290 --> 00:12:14.210
The time has finally come!

215
00:12:14.210 --> 00:12:16.010
At last, we get to fight!

216
00:12:16.010 --> 00:12:20.510
B-Boss Kyoshiro is one
of the Nine Red Scabbards?!

217
00:12:20.510 --> 00:12:23.010
Alert Onigashima immediately!

218
00:12:23.010 --> 00:12:24.560
Y-Yeah!

219
00:12:31.400 --> 00:12:32.730
Denjiro...

220
00:12:33.270 --> 00:12:34.570
Now then, Kin!

221
00:12:34.570 --> 00:12:35.150
Huh?

222
00:12:35.150 --> 00:12:37.820
I knew you were a clever man!

223
00:12:37.820 --> 00:12:42.280
This symbol implies the date
and rendezvous point for the great battle!

224
00:12:42.280 --> 00:12:44.660
Two birds ablaze…

225
00:12:45.240 --> 00:12:47.000
over a habu pit viper...

226
00:12:47.000 --> 00:12:51.130
and a reversed crescent moon
to signify rebellion!

227
00:12:51.130 --> 00:12:54.840
“The day of the Fire Festival. At twilight.
The second hour of the bird.

228
00:12:54.840 --> 00:12:57.260
At Habu Port."

229
00:12:57.260 --> 00:13:00.220
The original symbol didn't have those two lines.

230
00:13:01.760 --> 00:13:05.760
This flyer was leaked to Orochi's side...

231
00:13:06.520 --> 00:13:11.730
but Lord Yasuie altered
the symbol before he died!

232
00:13:11.730 --> 00:13:14.400
These two newly added lines...

233
00:13:14.400 --> 00:13:18.360
cross out the middle letters!

234
00:13:18.360 --> 00:13:23.030
So "Habuminato" without the middle part
means the new rendezvous point is...

235
00:13:18.360 --> 00:13:23.530
<b>Habuminato</b>

236
00:13:22.700 --> 00:13:22.780
<b>/</b>

237
